        "itineraryHtml": "<p><strong>SOUTH KOREA – SEOUL DELIGHT TOUR</strong></p><p><strong>Hotel:</strong> <em>Ibis Styles Ambassador Seoul Yongsan</em> (★★★★) or Similar<br /></p><p><strong>INCLUSIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Accommodation based on Family Twin (Double + Single) &amp; Double Bed share</li><li>All admission fees as per itinerary</li><li>Private transportation including airport transfers (rental car with driver)</li><li>English-speaking guide throughout the tour</li></ul><p><strong>EXCLUSIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Travel Insurance &amp; Visa processing</li><li>Lunches and Dinners</li><li>Tips for local guide and driver</li><li>Personal expenses and any items not mentioned under “Inclusions”</li></ul><p><strong>DETAILED ITINERARY</strong></p><p><strong>DAY 1 –ARRIVAL IN SEOUL</strong></p><p><strong>Meals:</strong> L – X | D – X</p><ul><li>Arrive at Incheon International Airport.</li><li>Meet and greet by our English-speaking guide.</li><li>Transfer to Seoul city.</li><li>Check-in at hotel and rest after your journey.<br /><strong>Overnight:</strong> Seoul</li></ul><p><strong>DAY 2 – SEOUL CITY DISCOVERY</strong></p><p><strong>Meals:</strong> B – Hotel | L – X | D – X</p><ul><li>Depart from hotel after breakfast.</li><li>Visit <strong>N-Seoul Tower</strong> (including Cable Car &amp; Observatory).</li><li>Explore <strong>Gyeongbokgung Palace</strong> (Optional Hanbok Rental – US$ 20 per person).</li><li>Walk through the traditional lanes of <strong>Bukchon Hanok Village</strong>.</li><li>Stop at <strong>Korean Ginseng Exhibition Center</strong> for local insights.</li><li>Stroll along <strong>Insadong Antique Alley</strong> – famous for art &amp; souvenirs.</li><li>Return to hotel.<br /><strong>Overnight:</strong> Seoul</li></ul><p><strong>DAY 3 –  MODERN SEOUL &amp; SHOPPING</strong></p><p><strong>Meals:</strong> B – Hotel | L – X | D – X</p><ul><li>Depart from hotel for a day of modern Seoul experiences.</li><li>Visit <strong>Times Square Mall</strong>, one of Seoul’s premier lifestyle complexes.</li><li>Enjoy <strong>Indoor Animal Theme Park</strong> – fun for all ages.</li><li>Free time at <strong>Myeongdong Shopping Street</strong> for fashion &amp; street food.</li><li>Visit <strong>HiKR Ground</strong>, a trendy hub for Hallyu (K-Pop &amp; K-Drama).</li><li>Explore <strong>The Hyundai Mall</strong>, a luxury retail destination.</li><li>Return to hotel.<br /><strong>Overnight:</strong> Seoul</li></ul><p><strong>DAY 4 – CULTURE &amp; ENTERTAINMENT</strong></p><p><strong>Meals:</strong> B – Hotel | L – X | D – X</p><ul><li>Visit <strong>Jogyesa Temple</strong>, a serene Buddhist landmark.</li><li>Explore <strong>COEX Mall</strong>, <strong>Gangnam Style Sculpture</strong>, and the <strong>Starfield Library</strong>.</li><li>Continue to <strong>Lotte World Mall</strong> for premium shopping and dining.</li><li>Enjoy panoramic views from <strong>Seoul Sky Observatory</strong> and visit the <strong>Aquarium</strong>.</li><li>Return to hotel.<br /><strong>Overnight:</strong> Seoul</li></ul><p><strong>DAY 5 – DEPARTURE DAY</strong></p><p><strong>Flight:</strong> TBA | <strong>Meals:</strong> B – Hotel | L – X | D – X</p><ul><li>Breakfast at the hotel.</li><li>Check out and transfer to <strong>Incheon International Airport</strong>.</li><li>End of services.<br /><strong>End of Tour with Beautiful Memories of Seoul!</strong></li></ul>"
